
Creating directories in hadoop file system

$ hadoop fs -mkdir -p /user/paolo/capstone/airline_origin_destination

Put origin-destination data in hadoop filesystem

$ hadoop fs -put ./raw_data/* /user/paolo/capstone/airline_origin_destination/

Listing directory contents

$ hadoop fs -ls /user/paolo/capstone/airline_origin_destination/
 
Call a pig script passing input directory and output file

$ pig -x mapreduce -p input=/user/paolo/capstone/airline_origin_destination/ -p output=/user/paolo/capstone/top_10 load_origin_destination.pig

List resuts in hadoop FS:

$ hadoop fs -ls /user/paolo/capstone/top_10/

Dump results on screeen:

$ hadoop fs -cat /user/paolo/capstone/top_10/part-r-00000